# Demo API Workshop

This project demonstrates a Kubernetes-friendly Java API for local development, CI/CD and debugging workflows.

## Local kind workflow

```bash
kind create cluster --wait 60s
docker build -t demo-api-workshop:dev .
kind load docker-image demo-api-workshop:dev
kubectl apply -f k8s/
kubectl rollout status deployment/demo-api
kubectl port-forward svc/demo-api 8080:80

# Local minikube workflow
minikube start
kubectl apply -f k8s/
minikube service demo-api --url

# Debug flow

Start with Kubernetes object state before entering the container.

kubectl get pods -A -o wide
kubectl describe pod <pod>
kubectl events --for pod/<pod>
kubectl logs <pod> -c app
kubectl logs <pod> -c app -p
kubectl get svc,endpointslices
kubectl describe svc demo-api
kubectl exec <pod> -c app -- printenv | sort
kubectl debug <pod> -it --image=busybox